        "content": "This dashboard visualises the **ngx-otel-rust** module's OTLP metrics via the OTel Collector \u2192 Prometheus \u2192 Grafana.\n\n**Phase 1 metrics:** request rate, connection states, request & response body sizes, upstream byte counts, and **request duration percentiles** (p50/p90/p99).\n\n**Two module defects fixed in this dashboard's module build:**\n1. **Temporality mislabel resolved.** The instrumented `http.*` metrics are now emitted with `AggregationTemporality=CUMULATIVE` and a fixed `StartTimestamp` anchored to the exporter start. The `transform/fix_temporality` collector workaround has been removed. Fixed in `metrics_fix(temporality)`: commit 3ea552e.\n2. **Request-duration measurement resolved.** `http.server.request.duration` now uses the nginx `$request_time` idiom (`(tp->sec - r->start_sec)*1000 + (tp->msec - r->start_msec)`) instead of the wrong `ngx_current_msec - r->start_msec` clock mismatch. Duration panels are back; p99 now returns a real sub-second value. Fixed in `metrics_fix(duration)`: commit 9e2138e.\n\n**Future (provisioned, behind compose profiles):** Loki datasource for **logs** (Phase 2) and Tempo for **traces** \u2014 see `demo/README.md`."
      }
    }
  ]
